node.text:
It takes human Nature to move the world forward. That’s why we’re spotlighting a new generation of heroes.

Together, we’re making a pledge to the future, to design the world we want to see, a greener tomorrow.

Get inspired, get involved.

Link in bio to learn about @MuralMoves @FlockTogether.World @DayunTang

#NatureNeedsHeroes #Timberland

node.text:
The planet has a problem. There’s too much carbon in the air and not enough in the ground. But don’t worry, we can help. 

How? By getting the natural materials we use - like leather, wool and cotton - from regenerative farming. 
Head to timberland.com to learn more.

🥰 Special thanks to our friends and partners @renature @felipebvillela @savoryinstitute @purprojet @terragenesisinternational @thousandhillslg @richardsgrassfed @kimmatsoukas @kalolatheu @quinnsnacks @applegate

#Timberland #Earthkeepers #RegenerativeLeather

node.text: Nature-inspired innovation doesn't get any more comfortable than our GreenStride™ soles.  Made with 75% renewable sugar cane and responsible rubber from trees to create a natural foam. It's total comfort with less impact. Head to timberland.com to explore more #GreenStride products.

Leather is at the root of our brand.
Through the adoption of practices such as waste reduction, efficient processing, and regenerative agriculture, we are exploring and testing new ways to lessen our impact on the Earth and, in the future, making it net positive.
Check out our #CraftedByNature Highlights to learn more about Responsible Leather practices. #Timberland #NatureNeedsHeroes #EcoInnovation
Cc: @christopher.raeburn

node.text:
Our world is changing, and we are responsible for that. 
But our choices can make a world of difference.
We can choose responsible products made with renewable materials.
We can plant trees and protect nature for generations to come.
We can make a real difference. Together.
#Timberland #NatureNeedsHeroes
